comment.author: 42400804@N05
comment._content: My maternal grandmother was a Canungra Franklin. She was the daughter of Henry William Franklin whose half-brother was George. George was a baby when he and his father Henry Franklin emigrated from Lincolnshire to Queensland aboard the "Parsee" in 1853. My mother was born at Wonglepong, previously Coburn, Lower Canungra. This is part of the property where her mother was born: www.flickr.com/photos/42400804@N05/6902303390/in/set-7215...
